During a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre discussed various topics, including reproductive rights, gas prices, Ukraine aid, Iran-Russia relations, student loans, and the Saudi Arabia-Russia oil issue. She highlighted President Biden's commitment to restoring reproductive rights, his plans to codify Roe v. Wade, and his efforts to lower gas prices. Jean-Pierre also mentioned ongoing discussions about providing assistance to Ukraine and addressing the challenges posed by Iran and Russia. She emphasized the administration's commitment to bringing home Americans wrongfully detained abroad, such as Brittney Griner, and reiterated the President's stance on the importance of democracy. Jean-Pierre acknowledged ongoing concerns about inflation and the economy and stated that the administration is working on ways to forgive privately held student loans. She also addressed questions about the potential for large campaign rallies and the possibility of the text of the legislative proposal on reproductive rights being made public.